Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}(minced or grated). Peel and dice half the @mandarin oranges{2} into bite-size pieces (set aside for use in Step 4). Zest and halve remaining orange. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}(chopped into bite-size pieces). Trim and halve @radishes{3}; thinly slice into half-moons.

Open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== Dressing ==

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together ginger, orange zest, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @honey{2%tsp}, half the @sesame oil{1%tsp}, remaining @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @olive oil{½%tbsp}, and juice from orange halves.

== Assembly ==

Add lettuce, @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz}, radishes, and half the @wonton strips{1%unit} to a #large bowl{}. Transfer chicken to bowl.

Add dressing and toss until evenly coated.

Divide chopped chicken salad between bowls. Top with diced orange and remaining wonton strips. Serve.